  "spans": [
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0001",
      "text": "INCITS xxx-200x Link Services Rev 1.61 November 3, 2006",
      "bbox": [
        301.08,
        37.27,
        539.95,
        47.32
      ],
      "block_index": 1,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0002",
      "text": " 167",
      "bbox": [
        518.28,
        723.59,
        537.71,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0003",
      "text": "The conditions under which ACK_0 is supported are defined in table 167 and described in the follow-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        540.03,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0004",
      "text": "ing text. ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        69.65,
        133.77,
        80.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0005",
      "text": "If one Nx_Port (e.g., Nx_Port A) is capable of receiving ACK_0 as a Sequence Initiator (word 0, bit 11",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        226.97,
        539.95,
        238.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0006",
      "text": "set to one) and the other Nx_Port (e.g., Nx_Port B) is capable of transmitting ACK_0 as a Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.97,
        539.95,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0007",
      "text": "Recipient (word 1, bit 31 set to one), ACK_0 is supported when Nx_Port A is the Sequence Initiator",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        250.97,
        539.97,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0008",
      "text": "and Nx_Port B is the Sequence Recipient.  Otherwise, ACK_0 shall not be supported while Nx_Port",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.97,
        540.01,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0009",
      "text": "A is the Sequence Initiator and Nx_Port B is the Sequence Recipient.  ACK_0 usage shall take pre-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        274.96,
        540.09,
        286.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0010",
      "text": "cedence over ACK_1.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        286.96,
        193.18,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0011",
      "text": "ACK_0 capability may be asymmetrical for a single Nx_Port (i.e., an Nx_Port may be capable pro-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        310.96,
        540.1,
        322.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0012",
      "text": "cessing ACK_0 as a Sequence Initiator, but not be capable of ACK_0 transmission as a Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        539.97,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0013",
      "text": "Recipient).  Similarly, an Nx_Port may be capable of generating ACK_0 as a Sequence Recipient,",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        334.96,
        539.97,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0014",
      "text": "but not be capable of ACK_0 reception as a Sequence Initiator.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        346.96,
        375.43,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0015",
      "text": "6.6.5.5.4  ACK generation assistance",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        269.82,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0016",
      "text": "0 = No ACK generation assistance is provided to Sequence Recipient.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.96,
        406.22,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0017",
      "text": "1 = ACK generation assistance is provided to Sequence Recipient.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        390.8,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0018",
      "text": "Usage of the ACK generation assistance bit (word 0, bit 9) is specified in FC-FS-2.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        430.96,
        459.82,
        442.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0019",
      "text": "6.6.5.5.5  Clock synchronization ELS capable",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        309.26,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0020",
      "text": "0 = Initiator does not have clock synchronization ELS capability",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        375.12,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0021",
      "text": "1 = Initiator has clock synchronization ELS capability",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        328.44,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0022",
      "text": "The Clock synchronization ELS capable bit (word 0, bit 4) is only meaningful from the Clock Synchro-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        514.96,
        540.01,
        526.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0023",
      "text": "nization Server well-known address (i.e., FFFFF6h).  This bit indicates support for the ELS method of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        540.09,
        538.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0024",
      "text": "Clock Synchronization.  If this bit is set to zero, the Nx_Port does not support the ELS method of",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        538.96,
        539.92,
        550.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0025",
      "text": "Clock Synchronization.  If this bit is set to one, the Nx_Port is capable of generating the CSU ELS",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        540.0,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0026",
      "text": "frames.  See FC-FS-2.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        196.49,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0027",
      "text": "6.6.5.6  Recipient control",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        586.96,
        213.74,
        598.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0028",
      "text": "6.6.5.6.1  Introduction",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        198.74,
        622.07
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0029",
      "text": "The Recipient Control Flags shall specify which protocols, policies or functions are supported by the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        635.02,
        539.93,
        646.14
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0030",
      "text": "Recipient Initiator function in the Nx_Port supplying the Service Parameters when acting as a recipi-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        540.07,
        658.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p186_s0031",
      "text": "ent of Data frames.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        659.02,
        180.9,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
